<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <%- include("./parts/head") %>
</head>

<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100">

  <!-- Navbar -->
  <%- include("./parts/navbar") %>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="container min-vh-100 bg-light shadow-lg border-start border-end border-dark-subtle">
      <div class="container-content">
        <!-- Hero Image -->
        <div class="row mb-3">
          <div class="col">
            <h3>Introduction</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row gap-3">
          <div class="col-md">
            <p>
              Wyrd is a tabletop roleplaying game for 2-6 players set in a grounded world of ancient ruins, dangerous
              frontiers, and forgotten mysteries. You play adventurers seeking fortune, knowledge, or purpose in a land
              where every expedition promises new discoveries, hidden dangers, and stories worth telling.
            </p>
            <p>
              At its heart, Wyrd is built around a simple philosophy: freedom without chaos. Its rules emphasize clear
              procedures over exception-based mechanics, reducing interruptions to look up niche interactions or debate
              rulings. Every major part of the game — from combat, exploration, intrigue, travel, research, and crafting
              —
              uses the same core mechanic. The unified framework produces predictable, transparent outcomes while still
              leaving room for creativity, choice, and emergent gameplay.
            </p>
            <h6 class="lora-semibold">Tools of the Trade</h6>
            <p>
              In addition to this guide, you will need a group of people, place to play, and a few essentials.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>
                A set of 3 six-sided dice (3d6)
              </li>
              <li>
                Your character sheet
              </li>
              <li>
                Something to take notes with
              </li>
              <li>
                Tokens for tracking status effects (optional)
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md">
            <h6 class="lora-semibold">Being the Game Master</h6>
            <p>
              The Game Master (GM) is the architect of the adventure. They describe what the players see, hear, and
              encounter and how the world responds to their actions.
            </p>
            <p>
              When something comes up that the rules do not cover directly, the GM makes an informed call and the game
              keeps moving. Running a game is less about preparation than it is about quick thinking. Chronica's unified
              roll handles nearly everything without needing a separate rule for every situation.
            </p>
            <h6 class="lora-semibold">Being a Player</h6>
            <p>
              Players control heroes in Chronica. As a player, you describe where your hero goes, what they do, and how
              they do it.
            </p>
            <p>
              When the outcome of an action is uncertain, you use the Universal Roll to determine the outcome.
              Everything else is conversation between the people at the table.
            </p>
            <p>
              Your hero is defined by their lineage, life path, and physical and mental capabilities. Throughout the
              game, you will face dangerous situations, make difficult decisions, and occasionally fail in ways that
              make for better stories than success would have.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

</body>

</html>